description: BOOM! The first arc of “RUMBLE” comes to an end with even more weirdness, some headbusting, a cool monster ritual, and fire! And—AND!!—the biggest surprise yet! The end of an arc, sure, but the beginning of a really bizarre kind of war!

Featuring breathtaking panoramas and haunting images, Battle Lines is an utterly original graphic history of a nation transformed by the Civil War. A collaboration between the award-winning historian Ari Kelman and the acclaimed graphic novelist Jonathan Fetter-Vorm, Battle Lines begins each chapter with an object, and each object tells its own story. These objects, both iconic and commonplace, join with a cast of soldiers, farmers, slaves, and well-known figures to trace an ambitious narrative that extends from the early rumblings of secession to the dark years of Reconstruction. A daring presentation of the war that nearly tore America apart, Battle Lines is a monumental achievement.
name: HC

volume.name: Battle Lines: A Graphic History of the Civil War

description: The out-of-this-world outlook of a down-to-earth bear! Benjamin Bear can always surprise his friends, whether it's by walking on his hands during a snowstorm or by using a tree as a parachute. His zany approach to life has earned him two Eisner Award nominations and bestseller status among kids everywhere. French star author Philippe Coudray continues to delight readers by bending the rules of common sense and breaking the laws of physics.
name: HC

description: Everything has gone to hell on Earth in 2069. Not only have the dead risen, but they're now robbing humans to finance their exodus to the moon. Fortunately, a bastion of humanity stands in their way, Freddy Merckx. Like a particularly good dark chocolate he's rich, strong, ugly, rude, and last, but definitely not least, Belgian! An action-packed adventure comedy for fans of space opera, zombified prehistoric animals, and insanely violent Belgians with bad dress sense. Concludes the series created by Jerry Frissen and Guy Davis, with newcomer Jorge Miguel taking over the art reins in this last volume.
name: Book 3: Houston, We Have A Problem

description: A heroic fantasy epic and rite of passage tale set in a mythical pre-glacial Antarctica. Antarctica 12,000 years ago - long before it becomes a frozen wasteland - is a thriving territory, divided into the kingdoms of Antarcia, Leng, and Valusia. When Antarcia's first lady vows to kill Jaemon, the bastard son of King Abarugon, the mysterious Sozer foils the plot and carries the infant to safety. Bearing the mysterious mark of the Atlanteans, Jaemon must unleash his true potential and fulfill both his and the continent's destinies.
name: HC

description:
As the full horror of the Soviet advance becomes clear, the little group of German refugees makes its way through the dark woods of East Prussia. Romance flares between our heroine and one of her saviors, but these German war heroes are not all they seem. And the road to salvation is a dangerous one, growing more so with every step along it. Part two of The Last German Winter, by Garth Ennis and Tomas Aira. Available with Regular & Wraparound Covers by Tomas Aria, and Good Girl Nose Art & Battle Damage Retailer Incentive Covers by Matt Martin.

Join the Garbage Pail Kids for a literally breathtaking foray into fantasy worlds, fairytale lands, and flatulent frontiers!

Revisit the pop-culture phenomenon from the minds of Art Spiegelman, Mark Newgarden, John Pound, and many others!

Featuring the most fantastical creators in alternative comics!

description: The fun continues as Lance Pertwillaby, star of The Pertwilaby Papers, embarks on a new journey in his life and starts a career as journalist for a local newspaper. Little does he know, though, that he'll soon be subjected to a mysterious substance which will cause him to develop super-powers. Louisville's new hero, Captain Kentucky, is born and subsequently tries to keep his hometown (and the entire nation) a safe place ... with more or less success. Join Lance in all 150 episodes of Don Rosa's classic superhero parody that originally appeared as a Saturday feature in the Louisville Times between 1979 and 1982. Dig into a huge amount of bonus features like additional comics, newspaper articles, ads and much more! Also included in this unique collector's edition are introductions by Don himself, his friend (and Captain Kentucky guest star) Ray Foushee and Hollywood producer Don Murphy!

Feb 1952

Throne For A Loss (6 pages) - Suzie wants Ferdie to babysit Angela so she can enter a roller skating competition with Gregory. Angela suggests that she and Ferdie go enter the competition on their own.

A Kick In The Plans (5 pages) - Suzie's father is on vacation and determined not to do anything during that vacation. However, that means Suzie has to do all of the household chores.

Information Please (1 page) - Angela peppers Suzie with questions about life.

White In The Night (1 page) - Ferdie learns the hard way why it's a good idea to wear white when walking at night.

Take It Easel (5 pages) - Ginger convinces her father to take up painting as a hobby, with disastrous results.

Out Of Sorts (1 page) - Suzie helps her friend sort strawberries over the phone.

Nurse To You (6 pages) - Ferdie goes to visit Suzie at her new job as a nursing attendant at the local hospital. There he slips on a wet floor and finds being a patient at this hospital can make you sick.

A Miss In The Dark (1 page) - Suzie and Ferdie take a Tunnel Of Love ride, but someone else ends up kissing Suzie.

A Long Dog Tale (6.5 pages) - Katy thinks Randolph is entertaining a beautiful French model.

Off Day (6 pages) - Suzie's father's day off is anything but restful.

Descent

The last phase of Operation Pharaoh is set in motion as Ra returns to Egypt to retrieve the book of Amal. Victoria and Remo discover a secret that will change them both forever.
name: Descent

description: Chapters 116-124
name: End of Term Time

description:
Perpetual Sunset

Chapter 06 of Avaiyo, Vol. 01

After centuries of slavery under the oppressive rule of the Tamiran Empire, the people of Xiltria could no longer bear such anguish. Through immeasurable losses and hardships, these suffering victims were finally able to win back their lands. By forming militias and unifying all slaves together under one flag they were eventually able to crush the Tamiran Empire who had conquered the world so long ago. The people now had a fresh start in life. With their new "free world" they finally have a chance to get what they've wanted from the very start...peace.

Their dreams have been realized. Regions. Countries. Nations have been restored to their former glory. All of Xiltria now works together. With their continued efforts to reshape the world it is a time of prosperity. However, the seeds of evil have endured. In the underbelly of society, subtle remnants of the exiled Tamiran Empire still live on...and are starting to give way towards a new threat.

It's been nearly eight years since the citizens of Xiltria regained their freedom. Sekken, a young man who lived through the carnage, travels the world in an attempt to suppress any threats that could endanger this new "free world."
name: Perpetual Sunset

description: It's the Avengers versus some of their all-time greatest foes! Powerful Asgardian artifacts are on Earth...but can the Avengers recover them before Loki? Contains four short stories featuring the villainous Red Skull, Attuma, Loki, MODOK, and more! This issue? MODOK and A.I.M. vs. Iron Man and Falcon!
name: Bros Before Foes

description: While Batman battles the spawn of an enemy long gone, Harley Quinn and the Penguin orchestrate another surprise for Bruce Wayne!
name: Roadkill Part 1 of 2

description: The Menaces Drop In, as Dennis and Gnasher present another classic comic collection. Prepare yourself for terrible trolls, homework horrors, vile vikings and soccer shockers! Menaces Unite!
name: Menaces Drop In!

volume.name: The Beano presents Dennis the Menace and Gnasher

description:
3 The Hard Way

"And you shall chase your enemies, and they shall fall before you by the sword..." (Leviticus 26:7)

Revenge is a dish best served cold as Jack, Billy and Cicada refuse to hide no longer. Due to a sudden twist of events, they take the offense in order to bring those who have betrayed them to justice.
name: 3 The Hard Way

description:
Introduced by your host, The Bloke, a Victorian undertaker, who I dress as at conventions to promote the magazine. Bloke's Terrible Tomb of Terror is a homage to the classic horror anthology magazines that we grew up loving.

This is an ongoing, self-published series, with eleven issues currently available and two collected editions. Voted Best Anthology Of 2013 in the Ghastly Awards.

The sky is a bird's domain

Chewler gets teamed up with a fearless airline pilot named Woody and sent on a mission to the Antarctic to stop eccentric billionaire Rubin Charles III from raising Adolf Hitler from the dead. Along the way they befriend a grizzly bear named Steven.

Drea becomes stranded in the desert as a red mist moves over the city. In this red night previously unknown connections and allegiances appear between all the major players. Hits, kidnappings, assaults, and double-crosses - all City War style.

Part 2 of 6
The Damage Incorporated crew get new outfits and take on a mission to stop invading space pirates.

A familiar resident is lost during a fight, and the blame gets placed directly onto Alex. When Alex makes a narrow escape, Devi rallies Old Coats, hunters, and other residents to create a lynch mob. Knowing that Devi won't stop until he's sent to The Wave, Alex pulls together his own army filled with monsters and wretched from The Prison.

This Ain't The Plague

Discover why the living dead are coming back to life. Encounter the corrupt citizens of the dusty town of Lynchburg as lumbering corpses descend upon them. Elsewhere, the stranger must use his wits to escape certain death.
name: This Ain't The Plague

description:
Getting Mighty Crowded

Dominic is almost killed by a horde of angry gnomes and his day just gets weirder from there.
name: Getting Mighty Crowded

description: The morning after Delia's fateful encounter, she realizes the short list of people to confide in consists of her ex-boyfriend and...nobody else.

El Cid. The legendary warrior of medieval Spain whose battles were a precursor for the upcoming Crusades in Europe and the Middle East. Banished from his own Kingdom, the ‘Cid’ continues to fight, at various times on the side of both Muslim and Christian to bring a nation into being. Amazing painted full color images by acclaimed noted artist Wayne Reid and written by award winning author Gary Reed. Part 2 of 2.

Under Stan Lee and Jack Kirby, FANTASTIC FOUR earned the tagline 'The World's Greatest Comic Magazine.' And there's no doubting it when you read the adventures they have in store for you in their third Omnibus collection! It's one history-making hit after another - the first appearances of the Kree, Annihilus and 'Him' (a.k.a. Adam Warlock); team-ups with the Inhumans and Silver Surfer; and the birth of Franklin Richards! Add in classic enemies Dr. Doom, the Mole Man and Galactus - and Crystal's first outing as a member of the FF - and you know what? 'The World's Greatest Comic Magazine' is an understatement. These are some of the greatest adventures of all time! Collecting FANTASTIC FOUR (1961) #61-93 and ANNUAL #5-7, and material from NOT BRAND ECHH #5-7.
name: Volume Three

description:
As The Fur Burns

Alex investigates his unsettling mental state. After a few unexpected encounters, he finds real blood on his hands.
name: As The Fur Burns

description:
The Grandmother Effect

Conflicts arise in the land of Justice as a new hero enters the fray and Fearless Man is forced to justify his awesomeness! As if it was not enough, worthless fathers and contemptuous hippies are making life more difficult for everyone! Damn you, Evil!
name: The Grandmother Effect

description:
In The Valley of Mists

With a battle raging between knights and nazis. Lt. Bell must find the pilot who crashed here with him. Things take an unexpected turn when he finally tracks down the elusive enemy. Meanwhile the rest of the crew, still scattered, struggle to find out what's happened to each other.
name: In The Valley of Mists

description: For over twenty years, Fred Perry's Gold Digger has brought readers a wealth of incredible stories and memorable characters. It's also been packed full of some of the weirdest, wildest, and most wonderful technology ever to leap off a drawing board. Now, in the GD Sourcebook tradition, we reveal the secrets and details of the fantastic array of gadgets, weaponry, vehicles, robots, and more, from cutting-edge discoveries to technology predating the entire universe...all told from the perspective of Gold Digger's foremost technology expert, Gina Diggers herself! From the Dynasty and Gaoblins' planet-sized Oblivion to their microscopic Symbiots and even a few of the inventions used by Gina herself! Join the machine revolution today!

In the GD Sourcebook tradition, we reveal the secrets and details of Gold Digger's fantastic array of gadgets, weaponry, vehicles, robots, and more...all told from the perspective of Gold Digger's foremost technology expert, Gina Diggers herself! From Gina's Hurt-bots to her tractor beam gauntlets, from the Leprechauns' Vaultron to the Mau-Tai Colossus!

While Earhart fights her way through the Elsewhere dimension, Lovecraft and Tesla spend an evening graverobbing before attending Mark Twain’s retirement party. The critically acclaimed Action Lab series continues!

Note: The digital edition (4/29/2015) for this issue was released before the print edition.

description:
Holy Cow Comics featuring Star-Spangled Danner

Who is that classic AMERICAN hero in the grand old tradition? Why, Star-Spangled Danner, of course! Watch in breathless awe as Danner conducts a nationwide manhunt for the alleged mastermind behind a heist at the U.S. Mint, Happy Ness! Yes, John Q. Danner has devoted his LIFE to LIBERTY and, now, the pursuit of HAPPY NESS! Also, neither rain nor sleet nor snow nor gloom of night will stop U.S. Male as he battles Slap Wilkerson! Hashtag Awesome!
name: Star-Spangled Danner

description:
Crazy Little Someone To Love

Love is crazy. And kind of cute. And has a tendency to urinate all over the house if you don't take it for regular walks. A lonely old man doesn't know quite what he's in for when he lets Love in, but Love has a way of turning frowns (and furniture and trash bins) upside down.

Love is ruff in "Crazy Little Someone to Love", story by Mario Candelaria; art by Mark Mullaney! Inspired by "Crazy Little Thing Called Love", this is the fifteenth story in KILLER QUEEN, A COMIC ANTHOLOGY. The digital file also features more Queen-inspired BONUS ART from artist Jason Folkes!

A tribute to the greatest band in Rock-n-Royalty, KILLER QUEEN features twenty-seven works from over forty artists and writers, challenged to rock out to their favorite Queen track and use it as inspiration for an original short comic or vignette. Edited by Enrica Jang
name: Crazy Little Someone to Love

description: Aten Ra meets with his friend, the Chinese doctor, and they reminisce about the former's romance with the doctor's daughter, who is the reincarnation of Ankesenamun (Aten Ra's wife in antiquity). A tale set in Egypt and London in 1928 with malignant exotic creatures, a megalomaniacal villain and a very strange relationship between two lovers. Don't miss this one!
name: The Devil Doctor

description: Is Walter's old pal Jonathan Holsten the one behind the killings? Jack, Morgan, and Walter face down the wealthy Brit.

The Apocalypse Party part 3

The cat's out of the bag. As Don's sister, Beth, and best friend, Jon, stumble upon Don's unusual nightly activities, they find themselves surrounded by ravenous hordes of flesh-munching nasties!

ALSO! The utterly embarrassing zombie hunter origin of Don Daniels!

And Kenny? He's torn between killing the undead and diving into a pint. Thirsty work this zombie-killing lark.
name: The Apocalypse Party Part 3

description: The conclusion to Bloodbath at Khe Sanh saga. "Sorry Charlie" Khe Sanh is protected and defended by US Marines but with terrible costs. The aftermath signifies a shift in US policy and the base is closed and dismantled. And in a surprise move to the American troops, President Johnson announces a restriction in bombing of North Vietnam.
name: Sorry Charlie

volume.name: Vietnam Journal: Bloodbath at Khe Sanh

Thrown Away

Nothing is as it seems. The vampires have been ridden from the town. But so to were the inhabitants.

Did Ethan succeed?
name: Thrown Away

description:
Revenge

Chapter Four: Welcome

In her search for The Fifteen and her past, Zoe seeks the assistance of an unlikely ally - Detective Wright, the policeman leading the manhunt after her.

Chapter Five: Revenge

Zoe comes face to face with the person responsible for her ending up in The Fifteen - her own mother.
name: Chapter Four: Welcome; Chapter Five: Revenge

description:
Peer over the edge of the Spider-Verse, at five different realities -- and five daringly different spiders! Spider-Man Noir returns, as the Peter Parker of the 1930s finds himself up against Mysterio and knee-deep in the biggest Spider-Man event of all! What is the secret of Dr. Aaron Aikman, the Spider-Man? Who are the villainous Red Eye and Naahmurah, and can Aaron live through Morlun's arrival? In a universe where the story you know becomes as horrific as possible, a radioactive spider bites a high-school nerd who is already something of a monster. Then, what or who is the incredible SP//dr? And finally, the breakout character of Spider-Verse makes her exciting debut -- in a world where the radioactive spider bit Gwen Stacy!

Collects Edge of Spider-Verse #1-5.
name: TPB

description:
Homecoming

Read about how as super heroine, Elisa Masters, returns home to start a new life as an "average joe". There are lots of surprises in this first issue.
name: Homecoming

volume.name: Amazonia: The Continuing Adventures of E

description: Take a drive in Archie’s run-down ride in this new digital exclusive collection! Even though Archie traded in his battered old jalopy, he hasn’t been able to shake his misfortune with cars! Join Archie and the rest of the Riverdale gang in this collection of car catastrophes. Maybe someone should just buy him a bus pass!
name: Car Crazy; Driving Me Crazy

description:
Prepare yourself for one of the most stellar creative periods in Avengers history! Roy Thomas, John Buscema, Gene Colan and Sal Buscema raise Earth's Mightiest Heroes to unheard-of heights with the debut of the Vision, an all-out battle with Ultron, and the introduction of Yellowjacket and an all-new Goliath! Then, Kang the Conqueror drops in from the 41st century, pitting our heroes against the Squadron Sinister in a cosmic chess match! As if one set of adversaries from across time wasn't enough, the Avengers must also battle the Captain America, Sub-Mariner and Human Torch of 1941! Also featuring the Black Panther vs. the Sons of the Serpent, the return of Quicksilver and the Scarlet Witch, and barbarian Arkon the Magnificent!

Collects Avengers (1963) #57-76, Marvel Super-Heroes (1967) #17.
name: TPB

volume.name: Avengers Epic Collection: Behold... The Vision

description: A tale of murder, motorcycle gangs, Charlie Manson, and the man who starred as TV's Marshal Hondo Bradley. California in the summer of '69 was a place of free love and hippie communes. But when Korean War Veteran and novelist Rory Hawkins spends the day interviewing George Clayton, former star of the hit TV western series Outlaw Pass, things take an unexpected turn when they cross paths with Charlie Manson at the Spahn movie ranch. Though this comic series is fiction many of the characters are real, and the story is rooted in historical fact, specifically Manson's desire to target celebrities for violence and his infamous residence at the Spahn movie ranch. Also, this series takes place during a very specific historical timeline (Saturday, August 2 - Monday, August 11, 1969), and the events are intertwined with the Sharon Tate and LaBianca family murders that took place during those days. It features meticulously research on the Manson murders and the narrative has been developed in a way so that the events in the story could be historically plausible and a resolution is reached without contradicting the historical record. Collects issues 1-7.
name: TPB

description: Part One of four stand alone stories from KJ Mendenhalls' Book of Monster Origins. Stories have long been told of the Pied Piper who leads kids through the deepest and darkest parts of the forest. But what happens when the children he is leading lose their way? Alone starts out as a feeding frenzy for the creatures that prey in these dark forest. But never underestimate your prey because a nudge in the right way can turn them into the hunters and you into their prey.
name: Alone!

description:
In the village of Dema, a Champion is magically chosen at random every ten years to uphold justice and defend the village against evil beings known as soul-takers. A new 10 year period has just begun and Kade has been chosen as the new Champion of Dema. Unfortunately for everyone Kade is a self-serving, tactless, opportunistic thief used to only looking out for himself.

He will gladly enjoy the celebrity status of being the Champion but has no intentions of taking on the responsibility or doing the work. Will the village be able to convince him to face his responsibilities? And will Kade learn to care about others and instead of just himself? Find out on the inside.

Champion of Dema is a fun fantasy adventure with an African theme to it as well as unusual creatures, cities and cultures.
name: GN

description: The girls are BACK! The ultra-popular Charmed Universe lives on in Zenescope's new season of the HIT comic book series. Piper, Pru and Paige return in Season 10 with all new twists, turns, drama, and fun that CHARMED fans have come to love.
name: Volume 1

description: Amidst the multitudes of tech-driven urbanites, in a society fused with electrical impulse and nano-scale circuitry, a rogue graffiti bandit tries desperately - and fails - to elude the cybernetic security squad bent on introducing him to the all-seeing MetaGrid. His only hope for the concrete jungle of his former reality may be the ultimate tech junkie, a green-haired systems hacker who extracts codes from plants in a homemade junk-filled lab; or perhaps a shady harem master who lives across the desert of waste mountains. And this might not be all bad, except for the twisty-turvey competition from his purple-skinned ninja ex-girlfriend, the diabolical and multi-faceted plots of the Queen of Binary, and the scythe of a genetically-engineered assassin looming about his throat. Welcome to Aztlan...

Empty Diary

There are events that, when happen at the right time, can create your destiny. Nesh, a lonely teen didn't know it and wouldn't understand it for a while, but what happened that day would trigger a series of events that would start his long journey, a journey of discovery, self-improvement and love that would take him to a destiny hidden to the eyes of reality...
name: Empty Diary

description: A Harvard-educated dandy and his blind, drunk companion are all that stand between the Old West and a Zombie Indian Apocalypse. The true story of Custer's Last Stand starts here... whatever they taught you in school is bullshit.
name: Part One
